<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–745:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 369<lb/><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting
                                            Secretary of State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-07">July 7,
                                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>3. The agreed recommendations submitted for your concurrence in
                                        <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName>’s 2441, July
                                        6,<note n="1" xml:id="d369fn1">
                                        <ref target="#d367">Document No. 367</ref>.</note> are in
                                    full conformity with the principles formulated in the
                                    instructions to <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName>
                                    prepared by the Informal Policy Committee on Germany, cleared
                                    with <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> and approved by the
                                    President. <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName>’s
                                    success in obtaining agreement of his Russian and British
                                    colleagues represents a considerable achievement. It is
                                    recommended that you communicate to <persName corresp="#p_PEW1">Pauley</persName> your concurrence and gratification.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                                        </persName>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>